orld championship silver medalist Letsile Tebogo and South Africa's Akani Simbine,Omanyala has run the fastest times.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1038, \"end\": 1043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999354259, \"rank\": 6.458288239589794e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1055, \"end\": 1063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999984224814, \"rank\": 1.5775094433788064e-09, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 1120, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999999049578, \"rank\": 9.106032606355208e-11, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1135, \"end\": 1148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sprinters\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 979}, {\"ngram\": \"African countries\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1002}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1034}, {\"ngram\": \"Omanyala\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest times\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His comeback from a doping ban imposed in 2017 to becoming the ninth-fastest man of all time has inspired Kenyans and has drawn more crowds to stadiums during national competitions.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": [], \"no