ngram\": \"positive drug tests\", \"from\": 2860, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's latest doping pariahs\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2932}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Omanyala received a 14-month suspension after testing positive for the prohibited substance betamethasone, a ban which could have cost him any chance of representing Kenya again.\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3101, \"end\": 3106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 1.371581817505331e-11, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Omanyala\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 2943}, {\"ngram\": \"a 14-month suspension\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 2974}, {\"ngram\": \"the prohibited substance betamethasone\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3040}, {\"ngram\": \"a ban\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"any chance\", \"from\": 3074, \"to\": 3084}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He maintains his case was a result of pain medication he received for a back injury and wasn't intentional doping.\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3229, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his case\", \"from\": 3128, \"to\": 3136}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3149}, {\"ngram\": \"pain medication\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3168}, {\"ngram\": \"a back injury\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3198}, {\"ngram\": \"intentional doping\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3228}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are those who do it intentionally,\\\" Omanyala concedes of the doping problem, but he adds: \\\"There are those who eat (contaminated) meat and they end up testing positive; there are those who walk into chemists or medication places and they are given medication that have steroids in them - (those) people you cannot put in the same bracket.\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3576, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Omanyala\", \"from\": 3274, \"to\": 3282}, {\"ngram\": \"the doping problem\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3313}, {\"ngram\": \"meat\", \"from\": 3368, \"to\": 3372}, {\"ngram\": \"chemists\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3445}, {\"ngram\": \"medication places\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3466}, {\"ngram\": \"medication\", \"from\": 3486, \"to\": 3496}, {\"ngram\": \"steroids\", \"from\": 3507, \"to\": 3515}, {\"ngram\": \"(those) people\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3540}, {\"ngram\": \"the same bracket\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Do not judge when you first hear an athlete has tested positive for banned substances, try to hear the story.\\\"\", \"from\": 3578, \"to\": 3689, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 3612, \"to\": 3622}, {\"ngram\": \"banned substances\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3664}, {\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes who are using performance enhancement drugs intentionally are making it difficult for the rest, he said, because any time a Kenyan athlete is running well there will be suspicion that they maybe on performance enhancers.\", \"from\": 3691, \"to\": 3920, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 3691, \"to\": 3699}, {\"ngram\": \"performance enhancement drugs\", \"from\": 3714, \"to\": 3743}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 3794}, {\"ngram\": \"a Kenyan athlete\", \"from\": 3822, \"to\": 3838}, {\"ngram\": \"suspicion\", \"from\": 3869, \"to\": 3878}, {\"ngram\": \"performance enhancers\", \"from\": 3898, \"to\": 3919}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barnaba Korir, an Athletics Kenya official, says authorities have ramped up education programs for young athletes across the country to help them understand the implications of doping and avoid it.\", \"from\": 3922, \"to\": 4119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3940, \"end\": 3955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athletics Kenya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Kenya\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Barnaba Korir\", \"from\": 3922, \"to\": 3935}, {\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 3971, \"to\": 3982}, {\"ngram\": \"education programs\", \"from\": 3998, \"to\": 4016}, {\"ngram\": \"young athletes\", \"from\": 4021, \"to\": 4035}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 4043, \"to\": 4054}, {\"ngram\": \"the implications\", \"from\": 4079, \"to\": 4095}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Poverty and unemployment are the main factors driving some athletes to use banned substances because they are trying to pull themselves and their families out of penury, Korir says, and will do so at all costs.\", \"from\": 4121, \"to\": 4331, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Poverty\", \"from\": 4121, \"to\": 4128}, {\"ngram\": \"unemployment\", \"from\": 4133, \"to\": 4145}, {\"ngram\": \"the main factors\", \"from\": 4150, \"to\": 4166}, {\"ngram\": \"some athletes\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4188}, {\"ngram\": \"banned substances\", \"from\": 4196, \"to\": 4213}, {\"ngram\": \"their families\", \"from\": 4261, \"to\": 4275}, {\"ngram\": \"penury\", \"from\": 4283, \"to\": 4289}, {\"ngram\": \"Korir\", \"from\": 4291, \"to\": 4296}, {\"ngram\": \"all costs\", \"from\": 4321, \"to\": 4330}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The concentration of talent also means that while some countries can focus testing on a small elite groups, Kenya has hundreds of distance runners capable of competing internationallyfrom middle distance to the marathon.\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4441, \"end\": 4446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 1.371581817505331e-11, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K